Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-brown; some mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Menekrates. Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.110, 38a. The original numbering conflated two stamps, 38b, not located and this.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0663)
